Modify the volume:
-----------------------------
Modify the type ,size ,and performance fo an EBS volume

Volume details: 
\_Volume ID
\_Volume type
\_Size
\_IOPS : IF supported
\_ThroughPUT:  IT supported 

Click MODIFY 

Create a Snapshot:
--------------------------------
Create a point-in-time snapshot to back up the data on an Amazon EBS volume  to Amazon S3 
Source Volume:
\_Volume ID
\_Availability Zone

Fixed

Snapshot details: 
\_Description
\_Encryption  : If enabeled for the Volume
\_Tags 

Click CREATE SNAPSHOT 

Create Snapshot Policy :
---------------------------------
This will take us to  LifeCycle manager > Select Policy type [Custom Policy] > Create a life cycle policy 

Speicfy the settings: 
Target resources:  Specify the resources that are to be targeted by this policy 
\_Target resource type : 
                     \_Volume
                     \_Instance
\_Target resource tags : 
                      \_Key an value of the targeted resource 
\_Description: Policy description 
\_IAM role :
            \_Default : If you are not sure 
            \_choose another role: If you want full control 
\_Policy Status :
                \_Enabel 
                \_Disabel 

Schedule details :
\_Schedule_name: 
\_Frequency 
           \_Daily
           \_Weekly 
           \_Montly 
           \_Custom core expression 
